(42, 12, 17, 42, 11, 41, 41, NULL, 'Connection of Generosity and Abundance', 'This connection highlights the theme of abundance and the importance of sharing. In Luke 12:17, the man is concerned about his excess fruits, while Luke 11:41 emphasizes giving alms from what one has.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 17, 42, 16, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Wealth and Stewardship', 'Both passages emphasize the management of resources. The first verse reflects a concern over abundance, while the second encourages using wealth wisely to build relationships for eternal benefit.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 17, 44, 16, 30, 30, NULL, 'Concern for Salvation', 'This connection highlights a sense of urgency in both passages. In Luke, the man is concerned about his lack of space for his fruits, while in Acts, the jailer urgently seeks guidance on how to be saved.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 18, 59, 3, 15, 15, 'build greater', 'Wisdom and Materialism Connection', 'This connection highlights the contrast between earthly pursuits and divine wisdom. The desire to ''build greater'' barns reflects a focus on material wealth, which James identifies as ''earthly, sensual, devilish'' wisdom.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 18, 59, 4, 15, 15, NULL, 'Planning Without God''s Will', 'This connection highlights the contrast between human planning and divine sovereignty. In Luke, the man plans to build greater barns, while James emphasizes the necessity of acknowledging God''s will in our plans.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 18, 42, 12, 21, 21, NULL, 'Wealth and Spiritual Richness', 'This connection highlights the contrast between material accumulation and spiritual wealth. Both passages emphasize the futility of laying up treasure for oneself without being rich toward God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 18, 42, 18, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Human Ambition', 'This connection highlights the theme of human ambition and self-reliance. In both passages, there is a focus on the decisions made by individuals regarding their possessions and authority.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 18, 19, 17, 14, 14, 'my goods', 'Connection of Material Wealth', 'Both passages emphasize the accumulation of goods and the focus on earthly treasures. Luke 12:18 speaks of building greater barns to store fruits and goods, while Psalms 17:14 mentions men who are filled with treasures and leave substance to their children.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 19, 20, 27, 1, 1, 'take thine ease, eat, drink, and be merry', 'Warning Against Complacency', 'This connection highlights the theme of uncertainty regarding the future. Both passages emphasize the folly of assuming security in material wealth and the unpredictability of life.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 19, 59, 4, 13, 15, 'take thine ease, eat, drink, and be merry', 'Connection of Life''s Uncertainty', 'Both passages emphasize the uncertainty of life and the folly of assuming future security. The SOURCE verse reflects a false sense of security in material wealth, while the TARGET passage warns against planning without acknowledging life''s unpredictability.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 19, 40, 6, 19, 21, 'take thine ease, eat, drink, and be merry', 'Connection of Earthly Treasures', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of accumulating earthly wealth. Luke 12:19 reflects a mindset of ease and indulgence, while Matthew 6:19-21 warns against storing treasures on earth, highlighting the importance of spiritual wealth.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 19, 46, 15, 32, 32, NULL, 'Connection of Hedonistic Themes', 'Both passages emphasize a hedonistic approach to life, suggesting a focus on immediate pleasure and indulgence. The phrase ''eat and drink'' appears in both contexts, highlighting a similar attitude towards life''s temporality.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 19, 21, 11, 9, 9, 'eat, drink, and be merry', 'Connection of Enjoyment and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of enjoying life, yet they also remind the reader of the eventual judgment from God. Luke 12:19 speaks to taking ease and enjoying goods, while Ecclesiastes 11:9 encourages rejoicing in youth but warns of accountability.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 19, 23, 5, 11, 11, 'take thine ease, eat, drink, and be merry', 'Contrast of Indulgence and Warning', 'This connection highlights the theme of indulgence in both passages. Luke 12:19 speaks of taking ease and enjoying life, while Isaiah 5:11 warns against excessive drinking and its consequences.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 19, 50, 3, 19, 19, 'eat, drink, and be merry', 'Connection of Earthly Focus', 'Both passages emphasize a focus on earthly pleasures and materialism. Luke 12:19 speaks of indulgence in ease and enjoyment, while Philippians 3:19 warns against those who mind earthly things.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 20, 18, 27, 8, 8, 'thy soul shall be required of thee', 'Connection of Soul and Wealth', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of earthly gains when one''s soul is required by God. They highlight the transient nature of material wealth in the face of mortality.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 20, 24, 17, 11, 11, 'Thou fool, this night thy soul shall be required of thee', 'Foolishness of Wealth Accumulation', 'This connection highlights the theme of foolishness associated with accumulating wealth without rightful means. Both passages emphasize that such actions lead to dire consequences, as seen in the fate of the fool in Luke and the warning in Jeremiah.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 20, 54, 6, 7, 7, NULL, 'The Futility of Material Wealth', 'Both passages emphasize the transient nature of earthly possessions. Luke 12:20 warns that one''s soul may be required unexpectedly, while 1 Timothy 6:7 states we can carry nothing out of this world, highlighting the futility of accumulating wealth.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 20, 19, 39, 6, 6, NULL, 'Vain Pursuit of Riches', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of accumulating wealth without regard for one''s soul. Luke 12:20 warns of the sudden loss of life, while Psalms 39:6 reflects on the vain nature of heaping up riches. This connection highlights the transient nature of material possessions.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 20, 59, 4, 14, 14, 'this night thy soul shall be required of thee', 'Life''s Transience and Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the fleeting nature of life and the inevitability of facing consequences for one''s actions. Luke 12:20 warns of the sudden demand for one''s soul, while James 4:14 describes life as a vapor that quickly vanishes.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 20, 18, 27, 16, 17, 'whose shall those things be', 'Wealth and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the futility of accumulating wealth without regard for one''s soul. Both passages emphasize that material possessions ultimately belong to others when one''s life is required.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 20, 19, 49, 17, 19, NULL, 'The Futility of Earthly Wealth', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of accumulating wealth, as neither the rich man''s possessions nor his glory can accompany him after death. This connection highlights the inevitability of mortality and the transient nature of earthly success.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 21, 40, 6, 19, 20, 'layeth up treasure for himself', 'Connection of Treasures and Riches', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prioritizing spiritual wealth over material possessions. They warn against accumulating earthly treasures that can be corrupted or stolen, urging believers to focus on heavenly treasures instead.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 21, 42, 12, 33, 33, 'rich toward God', 'Connection of Treasures and Almsgiving', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being ''rich toward God'' and storing up treasures in heaven. The first verse warns against accumulating earthly wealth, while the second encourages giving to others as a means of securing eternal treasure.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 21, 59, 2, 5, 5, 'rich toward God', 'Richness Toward God', 'Both passages emphasize the value of spiritual wealth over material accumulation. Luke highlights being ''rich toward God,'' while James notes that God has chosen the ''poor of this world rich in faith.''', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 21, 59, 5, 1, 3, 'rich toward God', 'Connection of Wealth and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of accumulating wealth without being ''rich toward God.'' They warn of the consequences of hoarding treasures, highlighting that earthly riches will ultimately decay and lead to misery.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 21, 54, 6, 18, 19, 'rich toward God', 'Richness Toward God', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being rich in good works and laying up treasures that align with eternal life. Luke 12:21 warns against hoarding for oneself, while 1 Timothy 6:18-19 encourages generosity and good deeds as a foundation for the future.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 21, 66, 2, 9, 9, 'is not rich toward God', 'Richness Toward God', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of true wealth. Luke highlights being ''rich toward God,'' while Revelation acknowledges spiritual richness despite physical poverty.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
